title: Grateful Dead Live at Richfield Coliseum on 1990-09-07
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Walkin' Blues, Ramble On Rose, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song, Picasso Moon, U.S. Blues

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Truckin', Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

Vince Welnick's first show.  Before Birdsong Jerry introduces Vince to the audience.

reviews.review_text:
Feelin' Groovy Writing about music is hard. Everybody says so. Describing how music sounds, articulating its subtle and often uniquely personal emotional effects, avoiding the idiosyncratic and persistent body of cliché that has gathered around the subject—these are problems that continue to bedevil the best professional music critics.
-- Keith Harris, (c) 2014 The Loft Literary Center

...so like, wow man, you gotta groove to this one.
